caption: Awesome!
Absolutely best on the quarter. They know us as regulars and service beyond the best. We live in quarter and without a doubt our favorite place to go. Salute to all the staff. Willi William crockett

The food was delicious and the service was amazing. The staff is very friendly, fun and made sure we were taken care of the entire time. Our server Stephanie was absolutely great. I would highly recommend this place

Orlando, Sean, and all the crew at Irene’s are top notch. So friendly and personable, they care about your experience. And the food is unbelievable. Steak. Lamb. Lasagna. So very good! This “hidden gem” is a must. And you gotta get the “pudding-esque” cheesecake!!
Great food, great service.

Irene's has become my favorite restaurant in the city.  Better than Commanders, better than many of the other higher-end staples.  It is the essence of Southern dining at its finest.  The wait staff are super accommodating, in that they love to see you enjoy your food.  They ask for your feedback, before it's not too late to remedy, if there's anything at all wrong (and there never is).  I enjoy the whole experience, from the brisk walk in the quarter, to the host, to the patio, to the crowd.  It's just a pleasant experience.  Thank you for always making my partner and I feel so welcomed, remembered, and served.
Fantastic restaurant in every way, price, service, location,and menu

This is our go-to place for special occasions!  We have celebrated at least 7 milestones here and the last, was just as exquisite as the first.  New location is beautiful - although I miss the quaintness of the ok’d spot - and they have retained most of the old location’s staff.  This last visit (15 year wedding anniversary) was wonderful - the escargot was buttery and decadent and the caprese salad was bright and fresh.  Our waiter suggested the whole snapper and it was PERFECT!  we just live it here!
Excellent food and service.

Great place . If the weather is nice go sit outside in the courtyard so nice ! Food was good . I recommend the specials they have for the evening . Disappointed about the appetizer with the fried oysters . I’m a chef  and I just don’t get the grapes on the plates used as garnish?  Our waiter Shawn was great !!

Irene’s was an absolute delight. Each starter was better than the last. The specials were out of this world, and the lamb was the absolute best I’ve ever had. I cannot wait to return and have another delightful meal. Thank you to our phenomenal, knowledgeable server, Dan, this is now our favorite restaurant in NOLA by a wide margin.

Excellent, with an interesting twist and seasoning from louisiana to France to Italy! Delicious

We were greeted by a very friendly staff and we were seated promptly by outside where we were given the option which was also beautiful and romantic. My girlfriend had the Osso buco which was delicious and I had the filet which was perfectly done. The staff was on point everyone was very friendly and attentive and we couldn't have asked for better service. Irene's never disappoints and is always consistently delicious.I would recommend Irene's to anyone who's looking for a really fantastic experience and meal!

Very good place for a date night.  With reservations we were seated promptly and the night was very good.  There are a nice selection of cocktails and the entrees are great.  I had the lamb and it was perfect.
My absolute favorite spot in the quarter.  I go atleast once a month.   The service is always exceptional  as us the food . Get a spot in the courtyard!

This place is magical. My wife and I went for a date night and it did not disappoint. The ambiance was perfect and the service was was excellent. Stephanie was our waitress and she made our night with her professional service and recommendations. I highly recommend Irenes’s if you are looking for a fine dining experience with top notch food and excellent service. We definitely will be back and I can’t wait.
The atmosphere is awesome.  The restaurant is beautiful.  The food is scrumptious.  Ms. Irene is the BOMB!!!.  If you have the opportunity to eat at this establishment, run, don't walk. Its awesome.

Came to NOLA for the first time. My boyfriend from NY and I from Miami. We did not know anything about this area and which restaurants to go so we picked the Irene. Called, made a reservation for 6:45pm, the gentleman on the phone was very nice and made the reservation for us and wished us a great evening and see you soon :) which was very nice. We arrive d on time and were greeted by Orlando the nice server who works there for more than 10 years. He was friendly and very welcoming. Then he gave us a table for two in a lovely side, our table served was Michael also a very nice and polite server. We had escargot with mushrooms, mussels in red sauce and duck meat. I would give 10 stars. For me the service is first thing I look at - I want to be treated as people are supposed to when they go to restaurant. There is nothing more I want to write besides - Thanking for great experience and food. Highly recommend
Excelent food and service

Food was fine. The problem was our waiter, Daniel who was extremely unprofessional, condescending, facetious, and rude the entire time we were seated. Daniel the waiter first started off with unprofessional remarks about one of the women at our table. He then went on to make rude statements about even the smallest of things that we did, such as bringing our wine glass closer to him (to make his job easier).  Halfway through dinner our candle was out of wax so we asked our waiter Daniel to get us a new one, which he replied “I can’t fix everything buddy” and never replaced our candle the rest of the night. Then the worst part of the night happened. One of our party members attempted to switch one of the smaller candles from another table, but our waiter Daniel noticed and asked him “What’s your name.” and then proceeded to yell out to the entire wing of the restaurant that our party member “...wants to take everyone’s candles! Everyone give him your candles!”  This public shaming went on for a good 2 minutes and included the entire wing of the restaurant laughing at us, with the table next to us (a group of regulars) turning on their iPhone flashlights, pointing them at us and saying “here’s some light for you.”  This wasn’t even the full extent of our horrible experience, Daniel continued to be rude almost every time he returned to our table.  If it wasn’t for Daniel, the night at Irene’s would have fine.

Disappointing experience. Waited 30 minutes past our reservation (we were there 5 minutes before) & saw others be seated before us.  Then our waiter, Daniel, was, i guess, being funny, & embarassed one of our party for trying to find a lit candle from an empty table so we could see our menus. Rosemary chicken was salty & tough.  Rotisserie chicken from costco is more tender.  I had high expectations & was very disappointed in our spoilt evening. We have been to Irenes before, but wont go again.

I don't know where to begin. If you are unsure where you want to sit, they will give you a tour to decide. Any questions on wines, they'll bring someone to your table to help with pairing. Lastly, they went the extra mile in bringing over a special birthday dessert for my partner in crime.  From the host, to the servers, to the outdoor ambience, and finally to the meal. Nothing but 5 star quality.  Thank you for the amazing experience.
Our favorite restaurant! The best food in the city with the best wait staff. We love going there!

We love Irene's and dinner was excellent as always. My spouse started with the Caesar Salad, I had the Grilled Asparagus with Prosciutto Parma- both excellent. The Meuniere Almondine was Black Drum that evening, a nice firm fish with mild flavor. The Shrimp & Crab Papparadelle had fresh shellfish in a lovely sauce. We went to Irene’s to have happy hour and an appetizer before our reservations somewhere else. Our service was amazing and our appetizers were so good we canceled our reservations and stayed for dinner.  We had the whole snapper, meatballs, raviolis, salads and crab dip and all of it was amazing.  Nothing could top the service though. Claudia was excellent. She told us so many stories about the restaurant and went above and beyond. Orlando was an excellent host. Everyone was so hospitable and pleasant we are trying to figure out how to go back in our three day stay.  Do not miss this place!!

From the atmosphere to the service to the food, FIVE stars all around. Chef Nicolas prepares some of the best dishes this city has ever seen (and that’s coming from a local). Also, thanks to our server Michael who was attentive to our drinks and food while providing a great atmosphere. Will certainly be back!

Outstanding. Make reservations.

Had high hopes for dinner at Irene's.  Restaurant is beautiful and we sat in a room that looked like a chapel and had appropriately distanced tables.  The patio seating with it's garden was also lovely.  I ordered the Mussels Marinara.  The mussels were the tiniest I have ever seen, but the broth was very good and after the mussels there was plenty of broth to dip the grilled bread in.  I ordered the lamb chops, which were good, but slightly overdone.  The garlic potatoes were a large mound and dense rather than fluffy.  The special of the evening was a filet with crab "ravioli" and a red wine demi glace.  The "ravioli" were actually crepes and not pasta.  Not very good and should have been noted as such.  Dessert was the hazelnut chocolate truffle, a very rich dessert, but marred by the use of whipped topping instead of real whipped cream.  I would rather have no topping than fake whipped cream.  Service was good, the atmosphere was very pleasing, but the food was a little underwhelming.

Had to grab dinner alone when my friends were tied up so two of us ran down to Irene's. The wait was long, but they managed to squeeze us in at the bar. I had skipped lunch, so we went a bit crazy with the food. Had the escargot, the corn and crab bisque, and the lamb.  The escargot isn't just a couple swimming in butter, but are inside a puff pastry, which is inside a mushroom cap and baked. It has a beurre blanc sauce that is awesome. A+++  The soup was an awesome corn and crab bisque. It was thick, almost like a stew, and had a great flavorful. Just a great filler on a rainy night.  The lamb was fairly standard but exceptionally well executed. Medium rare, with a dark, viscous demi glace on fresh garlic mashed potatoes. What could be wrong with that?  Finally we ended with banana's Foster bread pudding. Not too heavy, and just sweet enough to finish off the richness of the meal.  Great food!

A bit overrated from the previous reviews. My wife and I frequent NOLA. This was our first time trying this restaurant. The inside décor of the restaurant is extremely nice. But the night we were there the service level was way off. Our waiter was very professional but the amount of time to get our food took over an hour after we ordered. It was just my wife and myself in a nice but small room with three other tables. Each of those tables had 4+ people. A table of 7 were seated about 10 minutes after us. I know we ordered before they did. They received their food well before we did. Also, we noticed each of the tables were offered a complimentary liquor drink towards the end of their meal. Not that big of deal, but we weren’t offered anything. With the amount of restaurants in New Orleans in that area I can’t say that we will be back.
Amazing!

Outstanding!!! At first we couldn't get in but then we called and they found a table. The mussels were amazing,  cannelloni perfect and housemade, the chicken was great just a tad heavy on the salt, otherwise great! The sauce on the mussels was so good, once the mussels were gone, I didn't want to let the sauce go, it was perfect, light with onion, salt and pepper,not complicated understated, complementary to the mussels. The sauce was just like my mother ( straight from Italy) made for Christmas Eve Fish Dinner. We can't wait to come back to Irene's. Grazie del cuore💗🇮🇹🇮🇹🍷🍷🍷🍷

The fiance and I went to Irene's last night. They have hands down the best front of the house staff of any restaurant I've ever been to. The service was perfect. The food was equally superb. We started with the oysters Irene and an appetizer that was on special, the fried soft shell crab. The oysters were fresh, tasty and unique compared to the usual chargrilled oysters found in new orleans. The soft shell crab was fried to perfection and well seasoned. For our entre's we had the fish and the lamb. Both cooked to perfection. The lamb was exceptional, and the demiglaze didn't overpower the lamb, complimenting it perfectly. Her fish was outstanding, and the sweet potatoes were amazing. For dessert we had the creme broulee... I do not have a sweet tooth. The creme broulee wasn't too sweet and very enjoyable. Accompanying the meal we both had an imported Italian beer. The pilsner and the bock. The bock was AMAZING. we both highly recommend this place for a date. They bring fresh flowers and candle light to each table.
Very good Italian fare and service.

Anniversary dinner! Beautiful restaurant with a romantic and intimate atmosphere. From the pictures I thought the place was kind of casual, however, we were pleasantly surprised to find a much elegant restaurant. We tried the lasagna and the mussels, both great.  The LASAGNA was a solid dish. I wouldn’t say it was the best, but it was a good dish. The MUSSELS come with a heavy red marinara sauce. In my experience, Italians typically prepare this dish in a white wine / butter/ garlic sauce. This is not the case, but the mussels are delicious nevertheless.  The staff is friendly and kind. I would definitely recommend this restaurant.

I've been to a lot of restaurants and eaten a lot of steaks. The 8-ounce filet minion at Irene's was the best I've ever had. It was perfectly seasoned, cooked, and fork tender. The side of potatoes au gratin and sauce were fabulous as well. The wine list was excellent and included a wide selection of American and European wines at various prices. Additionally, our waiter, Darius, was once of the nicest and most sincere servers ever. He was amazingly helpful and friendly and boosted the meal to be one of my best ever. This is THE restaurant you need to eat at in one of America's great food cities.

Made reservations weeks ago for my sister-in-laws birthday. She had never been there before and I had spoken so highly of my past experience. Unfortunately, the experience was less than pleasant. I specifically asked that my regular waiter Dan waite on us, but the Manager Orlando purposely gave us Juan as our waiter, who seem to be less then competent to do the job. He was extremely absent and when he finally came around he managed to get our order wrong. We had to ask the bus boy Ricky twice to have Juan come to our table, which prove to be a futile effort. I brought it to the Orlando's attention but he basically smiled and dismissed it, by telling me to go back to my table. Service and food was fantastic! We were greeted like five times while waiting to be seated! Live piano music and dim lighting. Truly enjoyed the ambiance. Made reservations MONTHS ago.  Recommendation of a friend.  Both ordered filet mignon special.  Medium.  Came out raw the first time.  Came back about the same.   Sent back again.   Medium means warm pink center.  Not bloody and cold in the center.   When brought back I would have thought they’d serve a new steak that wasn’t cut into 3 or 4 pieces.  Not what I’d expect from a high end restaurant.  Very disappointed.  Was given sorbet complimentary.  But the damage was done.  Will not return.  The chef needs to invest in a meat thermometer.
Superb service and food!  I really enjoyed the beautiful watermelon salad, and cioppino. Checkout the courtyard while you are there...ooh, the duck is amazing--ask them to prepare it extra crispy.
Amazing mussels. Great quantity for a good price. Atmosphere was comfortable and upscale without being pretentious.

The staff, the food, the atmosphere; everything was on point here. From the very first second of walking in, until my last steps leaving, we were attended and taken care of by every staff member in the building. We let our waiter choose our dinner for us, and it was amazing. My girlfriend got the seafood soup, and I got the shrimp fettuccini. My waiter also paired us both with exceptional wine to match each dish. It was a wonderful experience, and every time I come back to New Orleans I will 100% come back to have dinner here. Truly amazing, thank you to everyone who contributed to such a wonderful evening!
Food and service is awesome.  Gluten free is definitely available and well taken care of.

WOW. This place is an absolute must while in New Orleans.  From the moment we walked in, we felt welcome and ready to have a great dining experience.  We were no disappointed!  All of the staff were friendly, funny and efficient.  The bar service was wonderful and the food spectacular!  Put Irene's on your dining list, you won't regret it.

This is by far the best Italian restaurant you will find. The service is unbelievable. From the moment you walk in, Orlando gives you a warm welcome and ensures that you are taken care of. The food is fresh and all made in house including the noodles. If you are a lasagne fan, this is your place! By far the best lasagne we have ever had. When you visit you have to request Christopher!  He goes above and beyond to ensure to have a wonderful experience and is very welcoming. We enjoyed this place so much we had to come one more time before we left.
Great food, reasonably priced, very friendly staff

Not to mention the quite large collage of overly opportunistic celebu-brag photos on the wall, which do not make the cuisine any more appealing.  Save yourself the price gouge and visit one of the other tastier options in the Quarter.

Irene's is our favorite local restaurant. Has the best food, ambience, and staff. This place is a "must try" for out-of-towners and a "go-to place" for locals. The new location is beautiful. We always enjoy our nights at Irene's.

Excellent all around. High class, professional waitstaff, incredible food.

Visiting N.O for the WW2 museum, a must. We had a short must dine at list from natives and Irene's made the cut. Large restaurant with big bar and nice vibe. Arrived on time for our reservation and directed to bar to wait. Nice bar, quick service, well crafted cocktails. Seated for dinner in a small side room with six tables. All had 6 people at essentially four tops. We were literally back to back with the tables on either side of us. You had to politely ask your neighbor to move if you needed to get up from the table Greeted by our server, Juan. Great guy working his butt off. Was not rushed with us. Took our dinner cocktail orders and our early wine order. Great drinks. had a couple of bottles of a delicius Amarone Shared appetizers, salads and entrees were delicious. No complaints. Steak specials temps were perfect Outstanding service, food, and restaurant with terrible seating for us and those around us. Highly recommended Just watch the size of your group and where you are seated so you can enjoy the delicious food Slainte

Last detail I'll add is the atmosphere here is great and what I'd call quite Nola: wood panelling, dark, low light, rich woods, very cool.

I have dined out all over the world from white linen table cloths to food trucks, and it is rare that a restaurant and their staff go above and beyond my expectations... because I usually expect a lot out of a nice meal.  However the folks at Irene’s exceeded any expectations and definitely went above and beyond.  My husband, 10 month old son, mother, niece, nephew, and I had dinner there last night and it is by far the best meal we have had in a long time!  The food (between the five adults we sampled most of the menu) was delicious and made it to the table in record time.  But more importantly they were so welcoming and accommodating of my son.  As soon as we walked through the door everyone smiled, said hello and welcome.  I don’t shy from taking my son to a nice restaurant because he is a good baby and I am usually prepared to deal with any of his needs.  But the servers were all so kind to him.  They all spoke to him, asked if he wanted or needed anything and Ms. Denise even brought him orange slices without us asking.  Dessert was amazing too, i has the creme brûlée and it might be the best one I’ve had outside of Paris.  It was smooth, creamy, and perfectly caramalized.  I will definitely be recommending Irene’s to anyone visiting NOLA!

Tucked away, we only noticed the sign because it has my wife’s name...Irene. This being our first night in New Orleans, we had wandered around looking for somewhere to eat, so seeing the name we knew it had to be a sign! We stood outside, listening to the nice music wafting out and beckoning us in. Without a reservation we expected to wait, but they found us somewhere immediately. We arrived at seven but within an hour the place was rammed full. The menu looked good and it was hard to choose what to eat. Coming from London we didn’t find the prices unreasonable, especially as the food was superb. Top marks. The wine list was comprehensive and reasonable too. Our waitress was attentive and friendly. Irene’s has a welcoming atmosphere and all the busy waiters had a smile or nod of recognition for us. Being picky, the air con was a tad too strong where we were sitting, especially if sitting underneath, but aside from that, the place is great. Thoroughly recommended.
